April 23, 2008.SHIJIAZHUANG, Apr. 22 (People.com.cn) (Reporter: Jiang Shan)Following approval by the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, the United Front Work Department of the CCP Central Committee has made arrangements for new and old leaders of the central committees of the various democratic parties as well as representatives without party affiliation to visit, study and hold a commemorative meeting from the 20th to the 21st in Xibaipo, the former seat of the CCP Central Committee, in commemoration of the 60th anniversary of the response of the democratic parties and non-affiliated individuals to the Chinese Communist Party's "May 1st Slogan".This is a major element of the series of activities launched by the national United Front system to commemorate the 60th anniversary of the "May 1st Slogan" and develop the theme of "passing the flame and creating the future together".